parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Frayed or damaged seatbelt webbing can lead to a failure of the seatbelt system, which can cause serious injury or even death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: seatbelt webbing separates completely during an accident
seatbelt does not restrain properly in a quick stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Malfunctioning seatbelt buckles can cause the seatbelt to unhook or not latch properly, which can lead to serious injury or even death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Seatbelt buckle unhooks the belt by itself
seatbelt buckle button cracks upon entry
male end of seatbelt won't insert into female portion

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inoperative or intermittent seatbelts can lead to a failure of the seatbelt system, which can cause serious injury or even death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Middle seatbelt on backseat will not buckle up
two rear outside buckles will only work intermittently

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Seatbelt to Retract or Lock
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the seatbelt to retract or lock can cause serious injury or even death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: seatbelt fails to hold the driver in an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Dealer Failure to Address Seatbelt Recalls
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of dealers to address seatbelt recalls can lead to a failure of the seatbelt system, which can cause serious injury or even death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Dealer refuses to work on seatbelt recall

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Oil Leaks and Crankshaft Seal Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine oil leaks can cause damage to engine components, lead to engine seizure, and potentially cause a fire, resulting in vehicle stalling or stranding in traffic.
symptoms: Oil leaks from the crankshaft seal onto the pulley

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Timing Chain and Chain Guard Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the timing chain and chain guard can cause engine damage, overheating, and loss of power, leading to vehicle stalling or stranding in traffic.
symptoms: oil leaked onto right front brake

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Overheating and Cooling System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine overheating can cause engine damage, seizure, and potentially lead to a fire, resulting in vehicle stalling or stranding in traffic.
symptoms: temperature gauge did not read hot

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the main engine seal can cause engine oil leaks, damage to engine components, and potentially lead to engine seizure or fire.

The transmission fluid leak can cause the transmission to shift harshly or hesitate, leading to loss of control, accidents, or strand the driver. It can also lead to premature transmission failure, resulting in costly repairs.

Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become stuck in gear, leading to accidents or leave the driver stranded. It can also result in costly repairs or even require replacement of the transmission.
